- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as random variables are a key concept in information theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as domain theory and probability theory are both areas of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as domain theory is used in the semantics of programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a less likely category, but possible as probabilistic models are often used in AI and machine learning.
